Russian Deputy Prime Minister Vitaly Mutko said it would not be long before the remaining Criteria of the World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA) and the re-edification of the Russian Anti-Doping Agency (RUSADA) would be implemented.
"At present, part of the criteria of the new plan has been finalised and RUSADA has already acquired the right to planning and testing in cooperation with the UK Anti-Doping Agency (UKAD).
